description: Barabas' trainee is inexplicably beamed away to the near future. Our friends immediately organize a rescue mission and travel after him. At the scene, it seems that big parts of the world have submerged due to global warming. Citizens can barely survive under harsh conditions. Even more when it is revealed that the rich want to keep the small pieces of land and don't back off to use cruel methods...
name: De Watersater

description: Wiske has a lecture about coffee and uses the Teletijdmachine to travel to the colonial past of the Dutch Indies. There she meets Eduard Douwes Dekker who wants to write a book about the repression of the people by the rich. The rich use the Ravana's gang to oppose the writer. Dekker becomes the victim of an attack and his manuscript falls into the wrong hands. Can Suske and Wiske prevent the destruction of Dekker's work?
name: De Halve Havelaar

description: The Zwarte Madam and her fiendish friends Kludde and Lange Wapper are on the loose. Sus Antigoon has taken away the magical powers of the madam and thus the trio plans their revenge. This time they target Antwerp, home of our friends. With a seemingly harmless stone and a magic potion, the villains are responsible for a spectaculair stunt that threatens the survival of the city...
name: De Stuivende Stad

description: One day, Lambik unknowingly beams an invisible ghost with him: the soul of a strange creature that used to live in ancient Greece. For years he's searching for his loved one and he becomes desparate. Ofcourse Suske and Wiske and their friends want to help the poor soul: they go to ancient Greece. There, king Demetrios want to conquer the town of Rhodos at whatever cost, even if it means the destruction of the souls in love. What follows is a whirling adventure in which our friends are pitted against several dangerous Greek creatures!
name: De Zappende Ziel

description: Barabas' greatgrandfather was falsely accused of a terrible crime. He seeks contact through a medium with the professor for his help. Barabas sents his friends to 19th century London to clear thing up. Soon it is revealed that Jabbertalk has an argument with the magician Spiritzo for years. The professor gets the visit of a burglar and shortly thereafter Queen Victoria is threatened with one of the professor's inventions, which makes her act really weird. Are there more shady people at work besides the illusionist Spiritzo?
name: De Kwakende Queen

description: Our heroes arrive in the Leiden of 1574. The city is, at that moment, attacked by the Spanish forces under leadership of one Valdez. He wants to hunger the city and thus force the Leidenaren to surrender. The situation drives its citizens to despair, but then help arrives in the form of Magdalena Moons. She and Valdez have feeling for each other, but she doesn't want anything to do with him as long as he attacks the city. Her niece Louise and a certain Francis cause trouble for the Spanish and take on a cunning traitor.
name: Het Lijdende Leiden

description: Poor king Bobbelbelly suffers from a deadly hiccup disease and sents for Papal Lambik's help. Papal claims that only a healing song can save the king. The men who have to perform the song are scattered over the African continent and, if that's not enough, can only sing if they have eaten a blue banana. And that bananatree is located in the middle of the jungle. What follows is a journey full of perils!
name: De Bananenzangers

description: Written like achildren'sbook each page starts with a letter from thealphabetin reverse alphabetical order, but it is far from appropriate for children. Congruity is non existent and all the pages seem random but after the whole thing is read it pieces together.
name: A Little Book of Alphabetic dispositions
Boven de pet van de wet

description: Jeffrey brown's own self-parody of his "ultra-sensitive" graphic novel, Clumsy. A heaping of in-your-face male chauvinism, over the top machismo, and self involved gratification. For all those jerks who complained that Jeffrey Brown was a sissy, finally you can see him be a man!
name: Hero of 'Clumsy'

description: Samuel, Forrest and Warren Kinsky, the younger brothers of Salomon Kinsky, obtained from the War Office an arrest warrant for Patrick Wilding, better known as Zagor. He is accused of murder. For Zagor, it's time to clarify many things...
name: Il Ponte dell'Arcobaleno

description: In a dark and rainy day, in Darkwood, Chico tells to Zagor the story of his life...
name: Cico Story

description: For the first time six funny friends of Cicos gather together to help the Mexican to achieve an impossible mission through all the scenarios of the most dangerous frontier: Indian forests, wild mountains infested with bandits, swirling rivers of rapids.. With him there are Trampy, the most likeable con man in North America, Drunky Duck, the Indian postman of Darkwood, Digging Bill, the treasure hunter, Bat Batterton, the most dilapidated of the detectives, Icaro La Plume, manufacturer of improbable flying machines, and Archimedes Zweinstein, the crazy inventor. If Cico alone is enough to get into trouble and create disasters, what can he do in such a group?
name: Cico & Company
